  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Assisting LGUs in Defining their Climate Action Plans</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The projects will conduct the following activities: 1. Local Climate Change Action Plan (LCCAP) Orientation at the local Government Unit (LGU) level before we go to the planning workshop 2. Deliver additional easy -to -use tools, info mix and processes that integrates tools from the Department of Interior and Local Government (DILG) LCCAP guide together with R1 learnings from LCCAP workshops since 2016 and emerging information (i.e. latest climate projections available, etc and latest discussion sessions with LGUs  3. Guide 1 -2 LGUs in actual community field research 4. Plan/conduct write shop for initial project proposals (e.g. Peoples Survival Fund (PSF) proposal) 5. Process assessment reports and conduct LCCAP Content Evaluation</narrative>
  </description>
